226
00:10:28.628 --> 00:10:31.796
You know. when Cam left. you stepped up.
but… but I stepped up too.

227
00:10:31.797 --> 00:10:34.799
And I love all my new responsibilities.
but I just really feel like...

228
00:10:34.800 --> 00:10:37.011
You're so right. You need a raise.

229
00:10:37.511 --> 00:10:40.889
And I'm gonna talk to Sandy about it.
I'm gonna make it my priority. I'm on it.

230
00:10:40.890 --> 00:10:42.807
Oh my God. Oh. thank you so much.

231
00:10:42.808 --> 00:10:46.353
This just means so much to me. especially
with Gene wanting to quit dentistry

232
00:10:46.354 --> 00:10:47.729
to pursue comedy full-time.

233
00:10:47.730 --> 00:10:51.067
- Hmm. Never made me laugh.
- He's never made anyone laugh.

234
00:10:51.692 --> 00:10:52.901
- Hey. Cam.
- Hey.

235
00:10:52.902 --> 00:10:54.194
Oh. uh. sorry.

236
00:10:54.195 --> 00:10:57.697
Hi. the clogged toilet is upstairs. Ness.

237
00:10:57.698 --> 00:10:58.948
What?

238
00:10:58.949 --> 00:11:02.619
Hey. he's not the fucking plumber.
This is my sober companion. Leroy.

239
00:11:02.620 --> 00:11:03.745
- Hey.
- Oh.

240
00:11:03.746 --> 00:11:05.705
Sorry. Good to meet you.

241
00:11:05.706 --> 00:11:08.917
Oh shit. you got a pool?
Could I borrow a bathing suit?

242
00:11:08.918 --> 00:11:10.460
Oh. I… I don't think we have any.

243
00:11:10.461 --> 00:11:13.505
Actually. you know what? I'm cool.
I can wear my tighty-whities.

244
00:11:13.506 --> 00:11:15.090
Oh. Uh… Hey. oh. Lev.

245
00:11:15.091 --> 00:11:19.010
Leroy here needs a bathing suit.
Do you have an extra one for him. please?

246
00:11:19.011 --> 00:11:19.970
Of course. You got it.

247
00:11:20.471 --> 00:11:21.513
Oh. Ooh.

248
00:11:21.514 --> 00:11:24.140
Hey. Leroy.
Yeah. I have a bathing suit for you.

249
00:11:24.141 --> 00:11:26.309
- You know. you can… you can keep it.
- What?

250
00:11:26.310 --> 00:11:29.020
Feel free to hop in the outdoor shower
before you jump in.

251
00:11:29.021 --> 00:11:30.564
What's up with the indoor shower though?

252
00:11:31.232 --> 00:11:32.733
That guy's amazing. He saved my life.

253
00:11:35.695 --> 00:11:37.904
You put him on every billboard in LA?

254
00:11:37.905 --> 00:11:40.156
I mean.
that's expansive outreach.

255
00:11:40.157 --> 00:11:44.202
- Are you still talking about Danny?
- Yeah. The offer will be ready on Monday.

256
00:11:44.203 --> 00:11:47.664
- Let's get it out as soon as possible.
- Great. I'll do that. Right?

257
00:11:47.665 --> 00:11:50.125
Oh. right.
that's if it's okay with you. boss.

258
00:11:50.126 --> 00:11:52.544
Yeah. Send it to me first.
and I'll take a look at it.

259
00:11:52.545 --> 00:11:54.713
I'd love to get
a text chain going with him.

260
00:11:54.714 --> 00:11:56.756
- Easy. I'll put us on a group chat.
- I love it.

261
00:11:56.757 --> 00:11:58.383
Hello. Okay. What about me?

262
00:11:58.384 --> 00:11:59.592
Danny's cool.

263
00:11:59.593 --> 00:12:02.429
- I wanna be on the chain.
- Oh. we never forget about you.

264
00:12:02.430 --> 00:12:04.848
- You're our guy. The ultimate cool guy.
- No. no. no.

265
00:12:04.849 --> 00:12:07.308
Don't <i>Gladiator</i> me. please.
Guys. our backs are turned.

266
00:12:07.309 --> 00:12:10.146
- Are you not entertained?
- Don't. please. No. No. no. no. no!

267
00:12:11.856 --> 00:12:13.106
Whoo!

268
00:12:13.107 --> 00:12:14.775
- Whoo!
- Oh!

269
00:12:15.693 --> 00:12:17.485
Can I be honest with you?

270
00:12:17.486 --> 00:12:19.863
I'm not there on this Danny thing.

271
00:12:19.864 --> 00:12:23.783
Well. on paper. he checks all the boxes.
and he's the hottest coach available.

272
00:12:23.784 --> 00:12:24.993
But. I mean. still your call.

273
00:12:24.994 --> 00:12:29.247
Isn't it weird
that he's. like. already Cam's guy?

274
00:12:30.166 --> 00:12:32.584
And he wants to change
everything we've built.

275
00:12:32.585 --> 00:12:35.044
Well. I mean. you just had
to be a decent human being

276
00:12:35.045 --> 00:12:37.298
and let Jay be with his children.

277
00:12:37.798 --> 00:12:40.133
Jay's like an extension of our family.

278
00:12:40.134 --> 00:12:43.511
I mean. he was a player
and then assistant. head coach.

279
00:12:43.512 --> 00:12:46.307
I just need someone
who understands this organization.

280
00:12:47.057 --> 00:12:49.309
Well. the head coach before Jay
was Bruce Adams.

281
00:12:49.310 --> 00:12:51.060
but he's dead. so that's a no-go.

282
00:12:51.061 --> 00:12:54.272
Jay always said
his real mentor was Norm Stinson.

283
00:12:54.273 --> 00:12:55.816
Wait.

284
00:12:56.484 --> 00:12:57.567
What ever happened to him?

285
00:12:57.568 --> 00:13:00.028
After he won a title
as an assistant coach for your dad.

286
00:13:00.029 --> 00:13:02.530
he was the head coach
in Orlando. Cleveland. then Detroit.

287
00:13:02.531 --> 00:13:04.032
Okay. where is he now?

288
00:13:04.033 --> 00:13:08.037
According to Wikipedia.
he currently resides in Anaheim.

289
00:13:09.121 --> 00:13:11.665
I wanna meet with him.
so send him the plane.

290
00:13:12.458 --> 00:13:13.792
It's a 45-minute drive.

291
00:13:13.793 --> 00:13:15.502
- Anaheim?
- Yeah.

292
00:13:15.503 --> 00:13:16.837
Then where am I thinking?

293
00:13:17.421 --> 00:13:18.297
I have no idea.

294
00:13:22.718 --> 00:13:24.344
Hey. are you guys decent?

295
00:13:24.345 --> 00:13:26.304
Because I got a VIP guest
about to come in.

296
00:13:26.305 --> 00:13:29.265
Oh. man. I can't be doing no more selfies
with your sponsor.

297
00:13:29.266 --> 00:13:31.768
It's not Dennis. dude. It's a girl..

298
00:13:31.769 --> 00:13:34.646
Okay. so put your clothes on. perverts.

299
00:13:34.647 --> 00:13:38.983
And allow me to introduce
my new bae. Zoé Debay.

300
00:13:40.236 --> 00:13:41.194
Hey. everyone.

301
00:13:41.195 --> 00:13:42.321
Ah. who is this woman?

302
00:13:42.905 --> 00:13:46.658
Benson. how do you not know Zoé Debay?
She had her own kids' show.

303
00:13:46.659 --> 00:13:50.370
Oh. I… I didn't watch a lot of TV
in Nigeria. I was popular.

304
00:13:50.371 --> 00:13:52.872
It was called <i>Triple Trouble.</i>
She played triplets.

305
00:13:52.873 --> 00:13:55.750
- Nice to meet you. Zoé.
- Miss Debay. big fan.

306
00:13:55.751 --> 00:13:57.210
It's an honor to meet you.

307
00:13:57.211 --> 00:13:58.753
I'm a big Waves fan.

308
00:13:58.754 --> 00:14:03.174
Y'all were robbed last year. but I know
you're getting that ring this year.

309
00:14:03.175 --> 00:14:05.301
Yeah!

310
00:14:05.302 --> 00:14:07.178
All right. enough.

311
00:14:07.179 --> 00:14:08.930
Zoé. the tour continues.

312
00:14:08.931 --> 00:14:10.849
Next up. HR and payroll.

313
00:14:12.393 --> 00:14:13.686
Oof!

314
00:14:16.814 --> 00:14:20.316
Can we hurry up? I have a pickleball match
in an hour with Stamos.

315
00:14:20.317 --> 00:14:24.404
- Oh. you made the connection. Nice.
- Guy covers the court like a gazelle.

316
00:14:24.405 --> 00:14:26.990
Danny finds out we're jerking off
another coach. he's gonna be pissed.

317
00:14:26.991 --> 00:14:28.116
and that's gonna be on you.

318
00:14:28.117 --> 00:14:31.286
Yeah. but I will say
Norm would be a lot cheaper than Danny.

319
00:14:31.287 --> 00:14:34.289
Yes. I just wanna exhaust
all possibilities.

320
00:14:34.290 --> 00:14:37.083
Jackie. you can bring Norm in now.

321
00:14:37.084 --> 00:14:39.253
He fell asleep in reception.
Should I wake him up?

322
00:14:39.837 --> 00:14:42.505
- No. he's… he's probably meditating.
- He was snoring.

323
00:14:42.506 --> 00:14:44.842
- Hmm.
- Jackie. just bring him in. please.

324
00:14:47.553 --> 00:14:50.138
Well. it's good
to see you kids again. huh?

325
00:14:50.139 --> 00:14:51.599
It's been a long time.

326
00:14:52.266 --> 00:14:56.227
All right. let's see.
Cam. glad to hear you're off of drugs.

327
00:14:56.228 --> 00:14:57.562
Yeah. that's a good call.

328
00:14:57.563 --> 00:15:00.815
Isla. Hey.
you're finally getting married. good.

329
00:15:00.816 --> 00:15:03.568
Yeah. you were single a long time.
so that's good.

330
00:15:03.569 --> 00:15:06.487
Ness. Asian wife. that's progress.

331
00:15:06.488 --> 00:15:09.700
And Sandy. you're. uh… gay.

332
00:15:10.659 --> 00:15:11.618
Yes.

333
00:15:11.619 --> 00:15:15.204
Yeah. Norm.
you've got a really impressive résumé.

334
00:15:15.205 --> 00:15:18.166
You have a .605 career winning percentage.

335
00:15:18.167 --> 00:15:20.752
five division titles
with three different teams.

336
00:15:20.753 --> 00:15:23.087
I mean. what have you
been up to these last years?

337
00:15:23.088 --> 00:15:25.673
Well. I got a condo in Anaheim.

338
00:15:25.674 --> 00:15:29.511
Yeah. right next to a Peet's Coffee shop.
so I go there every day.

339
00:15:30.721 --> 00:15:31.930
Anything else?

340
00:15:31.931 --> 00:15:34.807
I have a daughter. She lives in Boston.
doesn't talk to me anymore.

341
00:15:34.808 --> 00:15:36.434
Her husband. he doesn't work.

342
00:15:36.435 --> 00:15:40.355
and I refuse to call him
a "full-time dad."

343
00:15:40.356 --> 00:15:42.524
He wears a fedora.
Get the fuck out of here.

344
00:15:44.151 --> 00:15:49.822
Um. Norm. this last year in Detroit.
uh. do you want to tell us what happened?

345
00:15:49.823 --> 00:15:53.619
Well. let's just say I. uh.
I was dealing with some personal stuff.

346
00:15:54.370 --> 00:15:57.414
- Would you care to elaborate on that?
- No.

347
00:15:58.332 --> 00:16:01.459
We don't need to focus on the past.
Let's talk about the future.

348
00:16:01.460 --> 00:16:03.920
Norm. what do you think
about the state of our team?

349
00:16:03.921 --> 00:16:07.090
Yeah. what would you do
to. say. maximize player efficiency

350
00:16:07.091 --> 00:16:09.217
or improve our EFG?

351
00:16:09.218 --> 00:16:11.427
Well. I don't know
what any of that shit means.

352
00:16:11.428 --> 00:16:13.221
but what I'd say about your team…

353
00:16:13.222 --> 00:16:15.682
Okay. so Marcus.
you're paying him too much money.

354
00:16:15.683 --> 00:16:18.226
Travis holds onto the ball too damn long.

355
00:16:18.227 --> 00:16:21.896
And. oh well… Oh no. well.
you gave him too many corner threes.

356
00:16:21.897 --> 00:16:24.107
Yeah. Very. very sloppy.

357
00:16:24.108 --> 00:16:27.027
- Did we do anything right?
- Uh… let's see.

358
00:16:27.945 --> 00:16:30.072
Jay. great coach.

359
00:16:30.698 --> 00:16:32.115
I don't why you let him go.

360
00:16:32.116 --> 00:16:36.620
Oh. this is where my passwords are.
Now I can get back into my apps.

361
00:16:37.371 --> 00:16:39.289
I gotta buy some compression socks.

362
00:16:40.249 --> 00:16:43.794
Norm. it was great to catch up.
Thank you for coming in.

363
00:16:44.920 --> 00:16:48.047
Okay. all right.
Well. I gotta go anyway. I'm at a meter.

364
00:16:48.048 --> 00:16:50.091
I didn't put any money in
because I roll the dice.

365
00:16:50.092 --> 00:16:52.093
If you don't mind.
what's the deal with the snacks?

366
00:16:52.094 --> 00:16:54.637
- Oh. go ahead. Go ahead. help yourself.
- Really? Okay.

367
00:16:54.638 --> 00:16:56.806
This will go good with my coffee.

368
00:16:56.807 --> 00:16:59.100
- I'm a dunker.
- Just take 'em. Norm. Thanks for coming.

369
00:16:59.101 --> 00:17:00.893
- Okay. thank you.
- Bye. Norm.

370
00:17:00.894 --> 00:17:02.770
- All right.
- Can we hire Danny now.

371
00:17:02.771 --> 00:17:05.690
or are there other befuddled. broken men
you'd like to speak to?

372
00:17:05.691 --> 00:17:07.818
All right. fine. We'll go with Danny.

373
00:17:08.402 --> 00:17:10.028
- Can I go?
- Yep.

374
00:17:10.029 --> 00:17:11.488
Monica. call Stamos!

375
00:17:15.451 --> 00:17:16.326
Whoo!

376
00:17:17.036 --> 00:17:18.661
Where did Dollar Store Dyson go?

377
00:17:18.662 --> 00:17:20.079
I am feeling this.

378
00:17:20.080 --> 00:17:21.039
As you should.

379
00:17:21.040 --> 00:17:23.042
I might get a couple of these
while I'm here.

380
00:17:24.209 --> 00:17:27.587
- Oh my God. is that in pesos?
- Don't worry about the price.

381
00:17:27.588 --> 00:17:30.382
- Are you buying?
- No. Just don't worry about the price.

382
00:17:31.050 --> 00:17:33.468
I'm gonna go grab you some belts.
Chill here.

383
00:17:33.469 --> 00:17:35.596
Don't be asking anyone
about a bargain bin.

384
00:17:39.058 --> 00:17:41.517
Wow. looking good.

385
00:17:41.518 --> 00:17:43.978
Oh. hey. Zoé. What are you doing here?

386
00:17:43.979 --> 00:17:46.064
Just shopping.
You wanna know something crazy?

387
00:17:46.065 --> 00:17:49.567
I actually grew up
the biggest Long Beach Raccoons fan.

388
00:17:49.568 --> 00:17:51.819
- Really?
- Yeah. we couldn't afford Waves seats.

389
00:17:51.820 --> 00:17:55.615
The D-league gave free tickets to my
church. so we went to Raccoons games.

390
00:17:55.616 --> 00:17:57.909
- Oh. you've been to The Cage?
- Like a thousand times.

391
00:17:57.910 --> 00:17:59.410
I saw you play once.

392
00:17:59.411 --> 00:18:02.622
You were on fire.
but they had to stop the game at halftime

393
00:18:02.623 --> 00:18:04.832
because the team forgot
to pay the electric bill.

394
00:18:04.833 --> 00:18:06.793
Yeah. the owner was a real bad gambler.

395
00:18:06.794 --> 00:18:08.419
We gotta take a pic.

396
00:18:08.420 --> 00:18:11.006
- My dad'll freak when I tell him we met.
- Let's do it.

397
00:18:13.258 --> 00:18:16.177
Give me your phone
so I can share it.

398
00:18:16.178 --> 00:18:19.932
Okay. There. now you have my number.
So. are you gonna get this suit?

399
00:18:20.808 --> 00:18:24.228
I don't know.
I'm worried it's not nice enough.

400
00:18:24.812 --> 00:18:26.480
Mm. Well. that's too bad.

401
00:18:27.272 --> 00:18:28.356
You wear it well.

402
00:18:29.566 --> 00:18:31.359
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

403
00:18:31.360 --> 00:18:33.945
- So what are you doing after this?
- Just some shopping.

404
00:18:33.946 --> 00:18:37.031
Then I have a meeting later
about this movie my agent wants me to do.

405
00:18:37.032 --> 00:18:38.784
Wow. that is so cool.

406
00:18:44.123 --> 00:18:46.374
Isla. I have Danny Pierce's agent.
line two.

407
00:18:46.375 --> 00:18:50.420
Hey. Norm left this in my office.
Oh. sorry. I mean conference room.

408
00:18:53.757 --> 00:18:54.633
Holy shit.

409
00:18:55.342 --> 00:18:57.010
Isla. Danny's agent holding.

410
00:18:58.679 --> 00:19:00.596
Yeah. tell him I'll call him back.

411
00:19:08.897 --> 00:19:13.152
Hi. I'm looking for
a grouchy. older gentleman.

412
00:19:15.571 --> 00:19:16.905
Thank you.

413
00:19:20.242 --> 00:19:22.411
- Norm. Oh!
- Oh. shit!

414
00:19:23.704 --> 00:19:24.912
You can't do that.

415
00:19:24.913 --> 00:19:27.748
You can't sneak up on somebody like that.
I almost had a heart attack.

416
00:19:27.749 --> 00:19:29.000
I didn't sneak up on you.

417
00:19:29.001 --> 00:19:32.128
I gently tapped you
on the shoulder and lightly said. "Norm."

418
00:19:32.129 --> 00:19:35.339
I didn't know where
it was coming from. It was like a ghost.

419
00:19:35.340 --> 00:19:36.842
- Can I… Can I just sit down?
- Yeah.

420
00:19:37.968 --> 00:19:40.762
- What are you doing here?
- I am here to yell at you.

421
00:19:41.346 --> 00:19:44.182
I went to bat for you.
That interview was terrible.

422
00:19:44.183 --> 00:19:47.101
Your answers were all bad.
and honestly. you were kind of rude.

423
00:19:47.102 --> 00:19:50.479
Wait a minute. Is this about the snacks?
Because all of you said I could have them.

424
00:19:50.480 --> 00:19:53.775
You took everything.
an entire grocery bag of snacks.

425
00:19:56.361 --> 00:19:59.615
Norm. what happened in Detroit?

426
00:20:00.949 --> 00:20:04.077
And if I was to hire you. how would I know
that wouldn't happen again?

427
00:20:06.955 --> 00:20:09.790
Well. I don't think my wife can die twice.

428
00:20:15.714 --> 00:20:19.926
Yeah. my wife Andrea passed away
from ovarian cancer

429
00:20:19.927 --> 00:20:21.345
the last season that I coached.

430
00:20:22.387 --> 00:20:23.931
I'm so sorry. I…

431
00:20:27.935 --> 00:20:29.436
She got diagnosed

432
00:20:30.729 --> 00:20:35.150
and suddenly basketball became
very unimportant.

433
00:20:36.944 --> 00:20:40.113
Then when she passed. I kind of shut down.

434
00:20:41.698 --> 00:20:42.908
Started hanging out here.

435
00:20:45.619 --> 00:20:46.911
That's really tough.

436
00:20:46.912 --> 00:20:48.913
No. it's actually pretty nice

437
00:20:48.914 --> 00:20:51.582
because they gave me
my own copy of the bathroom key

438
00:20:51.583 --> 00:20:53.668
so I don't have to keep going up
and asking for it.

439
00:20:55.963 --> 00:20:57.381
You know. believe it or not.

440
00:20:58.715 --> 00:21:02.970
that meeting was the first time
I talked to other people in a while.

441
00:21:04.471 --> 00:21:05.429
I believe it.

442
00:21:07.808 --> 00:21:10.269
- You left your notebook.
- Oh. Oh. I left it?

443
00:21:11.103 --> 00:21:12.771
- Hmm.
- I may have taken a peek.

444
00:21:13.355 --> 00:21:16.274
You broke down all
of our defensive sets in the playoffs

445
00:21:16.275 --> 00:21:19.902
and basically reverse engineered them
for a new scheme.

446
00:21:19.903 --> 00:21:22.571
Yeah. well. I watched
every Waves game last season.

447
00:21:22.572 --> 00:21:25.116
So. you don't think
we should move to a man-to-man defense?

448
00:21:25.117 --> 00:21:27.535
No. no. You don't throw out
a system that works.

449
00:21:27.536 --> 00:21:30.705
You just shift the guard
to the high triangle with Marcus and Bugg.

450
00:21:30.706 --> 00:21:32.748
that's gonna shrink the floor on defense.

451
00:21:32.749 --> 00:21:34.792
Teams are gonna shoot 8% worse from deep.

452
00:21:34.793 --> 00:21:39.006
This way. Marcus doesn't have to sprint
like he's 25. It's too much wear and tear.

453
00:21:41.425 --> 00:21:42.968
No. you got a good team.

454
00:21:43.969 --> 00:21:44.803
Isla.

455
00:21:45.804 --> 00:21:48.598
And. uh. more importantly.

456
00:21:50.058 --> 00:21:51.101
they got you.

457
00:21:54.896 --> 00:21:57.274
I have a feeling
it wasn't a mistake you left this behind.

458
00:21:57.899 --> 00:22:00.610
Now give me your whisk.
It's a long drive home.

459
00:22:01.570 --> 00:22:04.488
- Yeah. thanks.
- You gotta jiggle the handle.

460
00:22:07.909 --> 00:22:09.493
Yo. D. hold up.

461
00:22:09.494 --> 00:22:11.495
- Yo.
- I wanna talk to you about something.

462
00:22:11.496 --> 00:22:12.830
Bro. I gotta talk to you too.

463
00:22:12.831 --> 00:22:15.916
I spent so much money on this suit.
I can't afford shoes.

464
00:22:15.917 --> 00:22:18.252
- Are high-tops okay?
- You… you're buying shoes.

465
00:22:18.253 --> 00:22:19.253
But…

466
00:22:19.254 --> 00:22:20.255
Ain't about that.

467
00:22:21.089 --> 00:22:22.507
I saw you sweating Zoé.

468
00:22:23.133 --> 00:22:25.885
- She's just a Raccoons fan.
- Let me tell you something.

469
00:22:25.886 --> 00:22:29.305
My first year in LA.
Ricky Smith broke his hand in practice.

470
00:22:29.306 --> 00:22:31.640
I remember that.
Took you guys out of the playoffs.

471
00:22:31.641 --> 00:22:34.978
What you don't know is. is that Ricky
broke it on Derek Newman's face.

472
00:22:35.479 --> 00:22:37.772
'Cause Derek was hooking up with his lady.

473
00:22:37.773 --> 00:22:39.566
And no. I'm not saying who it was.

474
00:22:40.942 --> 00:22:42.401
- Ashanti. Yeah.
- Damn.

475
00:22:42.402 --> 00:22:44.237
A month later. Ricky retired.

476
00:22:45.238 --> 00:22:48.908
And Ashanti left Derek for Nelly.
and I didn't get my playoff bonus check.

477
00:22:48.909 --> 00:22:51.035
There's a pecking order on the team.

478
00:22:51.036 --> 00:22:53.996
It goes me. and then about here is Travis.

479
00:22:53.997 --> 00:22:57.792
and then your broke ass is…
way down there somewhere.

480
00:22:57.793 --> 00:22:58.668
You feel me?

481
00:23:01.088 --> 00:23:04.090
All right. Well. good afternoon.
Thank you all for being here.

482
00:23:04.091 --> 00:23:06.550
It was a long search.

483
00:23:06.551 --> 00:23:10.097
but we always said
when we found the right guy. we'd know it.

484
00:23:10.597 --> 00:23:11.681
And we did.

485
00:23:12.182 --> 00:23:15.017
But then Isla wanted
to meet one more person.

486
00:23:15.018 --> 00:23:17.978
- So take it away. Isla.
- Thank you. Ness.

487
00:23:17.979 --> 00:23:21.441
I'm so excited
to welcome back Norm Stinson

488
00:23:22.025 --> 00:23:24.568
as the new head coach
of the Los Angeles Waves.

489
00:23:24.569 --> 00:23:25.569
Welcome home. Norm.

490
00:23:28.365 --> 00:23:30.950
All right. Well. let's open it up
to. uh. some questions here.

491
00:23:30.951 --> 00:23:32.618
Um. Rachel.

492
00:23:32.619 --> 00:23:34.954
Coach. there were reports
that some within the organization

493
00:23:34.955 --> 00:23:37.498
wanted to hire Danny Pierce.
but. ultimately. you were chosen.

494
00:23:37.499 --> 00:23:39.291
How does that make you feel?

495
00:23:39.292 --> 00:23:41.627
What do you mean. Danny Pierce?
Danny Pierce from Oklahoma?

496
00:23:41.628 --> 00:23:44.672
You... Seriously. you could've hired
Danny Pierce?

497
00:23:44.673 --> 00:23:45.965
Are you crazy?

498
00:23:45.966 --> 00:23:48.467
That kid's a hotshot. Yeah.
Easy on the eyes too. right?

499
00:23:48.468 --> 00:23:50.678
Norm is obviously joking.

500
00:23:50.679 --> 00:23:52.638
You're joking
'cause you're better than him.

501
00:23:52.639 --> 00:23:57.560
Look. I'm gonna do the best I can.
and. uh. we… we hope it goes well.

502
00:23:57.561 --> 00:24:00.813
But if it doesn't.
I guess it's on you then. right?

503
00:24:00.814 --> 00:24:02.982
Oh my God. Norm.

504
00:24:02.983 --> 00:24:07.194
All right. let's do another question here.
Coach Norm's gonna sit this one out. okay?

505
00:24:07.195 --> 00:24:09.113
God damn it.

506
00:24:09.114 --> 00:24:10.782
Dude. are you all right?

507
00:24:11.408 --> 00:24:13.033
Danny was gonna be my guy.

508
00:24:13.034 --> 00:24:16.412
He was gonna take us to the mountaintop.
and I was gonna get all the credit.

509
00:24:16.413 --> 00:24:18.832
Now Isla has thrown us this curveball.
Now I'm fucked!

510
00:24:19.416 --> 00:24:21.877
- What are you gonna do now?
- What do you think I wanna do now?

511
00:24:22.461 --> 00:24:25.546
- I wanna do some drugs.
- Yes! I was hoping you said that.

512
00:24:25.547 --> 00:24:28.717
I actually tried this stuff out
this morning. It's really good.

513
00:24:29.342 --> 00:24:30.301
Bottoms up.

514
00:24:35.515 --> 00:24:36.558
Whoo!

515
00:24:38.101 --> 00:24:39.060
All right.

516
00:24:43.440 --> 00:24:44.357
<i>Did you get it?</i>

517
00:24:48.403 --> 00:24:49.654
<i>Yeah. It's goof.</i>

518
00:24:51.281 --> 00:24:52.282
<i>I meant good!</i>

519
00:24:53.992 --> 00:24:55.952
<i>Yeah. well. you look "goof" in it.</i>

520
00:24:56.453 --> 00:24:57.871
{\an8}<i>Have a "goof" night.</i>

521
00:25:07.589 --> 00:25:10.841
- Hello?
- <i>Dyson. Clint Bonelli. Marcus's agent.</i>

522
00:25:10.842 --> 00:25:12.676
Ah. Yeah. we've met before.

523
00:25:12.677 --> 00:25:15.346
You were backing out of a handicapped spot
and ran over my bike.

524
00:25:15.347 --> 00:25:17.890
<i>Yeah. and I sent you home
in an Uber Black. didn't I?</i>

525
00:25:17.891 --> 00:25:20.351
<i>Look. you're becoming
a real asset to the team.</i>

526
00:25:20.352 --> 00:25:23.563
<i>I wanna ask you something.
Are you happy with your contract?</i>

527
00:25:29.486 --> 00:25:32.696
I made the Bella Hadid pasta from TikTok.

528
00:25:32.697 --> 00:25:36.200
We didn't have feta.
so I used the 365 Mexican cheese blend.

529
00:25:36.201 --> 00:25:38.202
Oh. thank you.

530
00:25:38.203 --> 00:25:41.038
Look. I know we said
that we were not drinking on weeknights.

531
00:25:41.039 --> 00:25:43.832
but I really could use.
like. three glasses of wine.

532
00:25:43.833 --> 00:25:47.586
I had a feeling. Hey. uh. by the way.
congrats on hiring Norm.

533
00:25:47.587 --> 00:25:48.629
He seems great.

534
00:25:48.630 --> 00:25:51.507
Yeah. well. he better be
because it's on me if he isn't.

535
00:25:51.508 --> 00:25:55.636
Ooh. that reminds me. Did you see
that photo of Jay Brown on TMZ Sports?

536
00:25:55.637 --> 00:25:58.597
- What? No.
- Yeah. my phlebotomist showed it to me.

537
00:25:58.598 --> 00:26:00.599
Apparently. he's dating
Miss Massachusetts.

538
00:26:00.600 --> 00:26:04.770
- He posted a selfie of them at a benefit.
- Jay Brown's dating a beauty queen?

539
00:26:04.771 --> 00:26:07.398
I guess some women
find him handsome.

540
00:26:07.399 --> 00:26:10.943
What? I thought he was supposed to be
like this intellectual guy

541
00:26:10.944 --> 00:26:13.779
who cared more about character than that.
But whatever.

542
00:26:13.780 --> 00:26:15.323
She's very pretty.

543
00:26:16.032 --> 00:26:17.659
Yeah. well…

544
00:26:18.159 --> 00:26:20.036
I know someone prettier.

545
00:26:27.210 --> 00:26:30.171
- Let's go upstairs.
- Why do we need to go upstairs?

546
00:26:35.218 --> 00:26:37.219
{\an8}<i>I mean.
they had Danny Pierce on a platter.</i>

547
00:26:37.220 --> 00:26:40.556
{\an8}<i>and I don't care what your pronouns are.
everybody wants this kid.</i>

548
00:26:40.557 --> 00:26:43.058
{\an8}<i>and they decide to go with Norm Stinson?</i>

549
00:26:43.059 --> 00:26:45.060
{\an8}<i>I mean. was he half-off at a garage sale?</i>

550
00:26:45.061 --> 00:26:48.522
He doesn't have a garage.
He lives in a condo. you idiot.

551
00:26:48.523 --> 00:26:50.149
Hey. you have a minute?

552
00:26:50.150 --> 00:26:53.068
I know he can't hear me.
I have to stop doing that. What's up?

553
00:26:53.069 --> 00:26:55.237
I wanted to see if you
got a chance to talk to Sandy.

554
00:26:55.238 --> 00:27:00.076
Oh! Oh my God. I forgot. I'm sorry.
Hiring Norm has been my priority.

555
00:27:00.702 --> 00:27:02.662
Not that you're not important.

556
00:27:03.455 --> 00:27:06.373
- Well. hopefully I'm next.
- You know. you are.

557
00:27:06.374 --> 00:27:10.712
I mean. things are finally starting
to settle down. not so crazy. so…

558
00:27:11.379 --> 00:27:13.714
{\an8}<i>Breaking news here. Breaking news.</i>

559
00:27:13.715 --> 00:27:17.926
{\an8}<i>Sources are telling me that with
only weeks left before the season starts.</i>

560
00:27:17.927 --> 00:27:23.891
{\an8}<i>LA Waves small forward Dyson Gibbs
is holding out for a new contract.</i>

561
00:27:23.892 --> 00:27:25.434
Are you kidding me?

562
00:27:25.435 --> 00:27:28.854
Jackie. I need my brothers
in here immediately.

563
00:27:28.855 --> 00:27:30.939
- <i>This is a repeat of last year.</i>
- Are we good?

564
00:27:30.940 --> 00:27:31.940
Yeah. we're good.

565
00:27:31.941 --> 00:27:34.109
- Did you know about this? You didn't know?
- No.

566
00:27:34.110 --> 00:27:36.612
- I knew about it and didn't talk to you.
- Does anyone know?

567
00:27:36.613 --> 00:27:39.156
- Not enough time to close a new contract.
- No. no. no.

568
00:27:39.157 --> 00:27:41.825
Why don't we put Sean Murphy
on the payroll at this point?

569
00:27:41.826 --> 00:27:43.661
We got two weeks.
That's plenty of time.

570
00:27:43.662 --> 00:27:44.703
If you're lucky.

571
00:27:44.704 --> 00:27:46.664
- Hey. hey.
- You need to handle this.

571
